From: Sven Sager <s.sager@kunbus.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Jul 2024 08:07:24 +0200
Subject: patch: Change executable folder von bin to sbin

In the old versions for Bullseye, the application was always stored in
/usr/sbin. This behavior is maintained and the systemd unit file must
be adjusted.

Signed-off-by: Sven Sager <s.sager@kunbus.com>
---
 data/systemd/noderedrevpinodes-server.service | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/data/systemd/noderedrevpinodes-server.service b/data/systemd/noderedrevpinodes-server.service
index fcc1f01..ef2b527 100644
--- a/data/systemd/noderedrevpinodes-server.service
+++ b/data/systemd/noderedrevpinodes-server.service
@@ -9,7 +9,7 @@ MemoryMax=400M
 
 [Service]
 Type=simple
-ExecStart=/usr/bin/sh -c 'exec /usr/bin/noderedrevpinodes-server 2>> /var/log/revpi-server.log'
+ExecStart=/usr/bin/sh -c 'exec /usr/sbin/noderedrevpinodes-server 2>> /var/log/revpi-server.log'
 WorkingDirectory=/usr/share/noderedrevpinodes-server/
 Restart=on-abort
 
